      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">2/6/88 ¶  ¶ Next week, noble Friend, the box with insects goes off to Messrs Watson &amp; Scull for you. I have succeeded in obtaining a ¶  ¶ Leipoa ¶  ¶ ♂ ¶ , adult, ¶ Mound-building bird, commonly calle...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.06.02a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Ferdinand von Krauss</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Stuttgart.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotations by Krauss: 'Weiter erhalten v. Broinowski Birds of Australia No 5.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">6 vol. III in Juli 88. durch v. Müller. Empf 23 Juli. Rep. 16 Aug.'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>[Further received Broinowski<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Birds of Australia</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>nos. 5, 6, vol. III in July 88 through von Mueller. Received 23 July. Reply 16 Aug]. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>2/6/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nächste Woche, edler Freund, geht die Kiste mit Insekten an Mess Watson &amp; Scull für Sie ab. Es ist mir gelungen, eine<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Leipoa</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♂</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>erwachsen, zu erlangen, nicht aber den Thylacinus, noch den Dingo. Sind Sie überzeugt, dass die früheren Dingos Bastarde waren? Ich bezweifle es, denn der zahme Hund ist dem Dingo stets feindlich u Variätäten kommen auch bei Letzteren vor.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Die Insekten Sammlung habe ich für eine<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">bedeutende</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Summe von Mr French<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">gekauft</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">; es ist also eine Schenkung allein von mir. Indessen wünscht er gern für seine Belehrung ein Ex von solchen Arten zurück, von denen reichlich da ist.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Diese Rücksendung wird Ihnen wohl nicht gar zu schwer fallen, zumal da Watson &amp; Scull solche von London aus expediren können. Es ist<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nicht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>nöthig,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">viele</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Arten nach Mr French zu nennen, da er nicht immer selbst der Sammler war, sondern viel tauschte mit den Mitgliedern des hiesigen Field Naturalists Club, deren<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Patron</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ich bin.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wenn ich aber bitte, dass die<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Bearbeitung bald</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>geschehe u so die<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Veröffentlichung</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>auch, so ist es im Interesse Ihrer Entomologen, denn in Sydney bilden sich nach u nach Monographen auch für alle Klassen der Insekten heran.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit freundschaftlichen Grusse der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2/6/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Next week, noble Friend, the box with insects goes off to Messrs Watson &amp; Scull for you. I have succeeded in obtaining a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Leipoa</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♂</seg>, adult,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Mound-building bird, commonly called 'Mallee fowl'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but not the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Thylacinus</seg>,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Marsupial, commonly called 'Tasmanian Tiger'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>nor the Dingo. Are you convinced that the earlier Dingos were hybrids? I doubt it, because the tame dog is always hostile to the Dingo and varieties occur even in the latter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">purchased</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the insect collection for a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">considerable</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sum from Mr French;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Charles French Snr.<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">See M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">F. von<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Krauss</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>4 May 1888</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">in this edition as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">88-05-04c</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it is therefore a present from me alone. Nevertheless he wants very much to receive back for his instruction a specimen of such species of which there are ample there.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This return consignment will probably not fall on you too heavily at all, especially since Watson &amp; Scull can dispatch it on from London. It is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>necessary to name<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">many</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>species after Mr French, since he was not always the collector himself, but exchanged many with the members of the local Field Naturalists' Club, of which I am<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Patron</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>However, if I ask that the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">working up</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>happen<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">soon</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and so also the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">publication</hi>
               </seg>, it is in the interests of your entomologists, because in Sydney monographers are also training themselves gradually for all classes of insects.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No species named after French by German entomologists<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>listed in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="https://biodiversity.org.au/afd/">
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0563C1; ">Austr</seg>
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0563C1; ">a</seg>
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0563C1; ">lian faunal directory</seg>
                        </ref>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(accessed 26 April 2022).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With amiable greetings your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
